                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/641.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 57.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 48 of February 8
                    last, I regret to have to say that the Nicaraguan Government shows itself
                    reluctant to divulge additional explanatory information. In view of its
                    unwillingness and the difficulties encountered in persuading it to furnish the
                    statements enclosed with the above-mentioned despatch, I deem it unwise to
                    insist at this time on a supplementary explanation of the enclosures
                    thereto.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Benjamin L. Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
